      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/94/1",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اِمْرَأَةٍ لَهَا زَوْجٌ وَ هِيَ صَرُورَةٌ وَ لاَ يَأْذَنُ لَهَا فِي اَلْحَجِّ قَالَ «تَحُجُّ وَ إِنْ لَمْ يَأْذَنْ لَهَا »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2907 - Aban narrated from Zurara, from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\nI asked him about a woman who has a husband, has not performed Hajj before (ṣarūra), and her husband does not permit her to go for Hajj.\nImam (as) said: \"She should perform Hajj, even if he does not permit her.\""
        ]
      }
    },
